NAME
	xor - XOR files

SYNOPSIS
	xor [STRING]

DESCRIPTION
	Performs XOR on data provided by stdin with a provided string STRING, and
	prints the resulting data to stdout. STRING is repeated and/or cropped as
	necessary to equal the data's length.
	If STRING is omitted, xor performs XOR on the data with all bits set to 1.

EXAMPLE
	xor 'mypassphrase' < porn.tgz > scrambled_porn_muahaha

RETURNS
	If the wrong number of arguments (more than 1) is given, xor returns
	EXIT_FAILURE as defined in the C standard library; otherwise xor shall
	return 0.
